## 2. Agent Identity Descriptor (AID)

The AID is the agent's signed passport. It declares what the agent perceives, what it
controls, how it reasons, and what its authority boundaries are.

### 2.1 AID Schema

```json
{
  "uid":          "string — globally unique, format: agt-{platform}-{role}-{index}",
  "name":         "string — human-readable name",
  "version":      "string — semver",
  "tier":         "integer (1=fast/edge, 2=medium, 3=sovereign/cloud)",
  "platform":     "string — platform identifier this agent operates on",

  "perceives": ["list of path prefixes this agent subscribes to"],
  "controls":  ["list of path prefixes this agent may write (cmd.* paths only)"],

  "reasoning": {
    "model_id":              "string — model name or 'deterministic'",
    "inference_engine":      "string — llama.cpp | hailo-sdk | rule-engine | etc.",
    "max_latency_ms":        "integer — worst-case reasoning latency",
    "context_budget_tokens": "integer — max tokens this agent may use per decision",
    "world_model_token_budget": "integer — max tokens for world model context"
  },

  "trust": {
    "initial_identity_trust":   "float — assigned at registration by sovereign/operator",
    "initial_behavioral_trust": "float — defaults to 0.50 for new agents",
    "authority_scope":          ["list of cmd.* path prefixes this agent may issue"]
  },

  "safety": {
    "human_override_path":    "string — meta path checked before any cmd.* write",
    "confidence_threshold":   "float — minimum internal confidence before actuation",
    "fallback_action":        "string — what to do if negotiation fails (see §7.4)",
    "max_consecutive_actions": "integer — circuit breaker: halt after N actions without human confirm"
  },

  "comms": {
    "heartbeat_interval_s": "integer — how often to publish HEARTBEAT",
    "announce_on_startup":  "bool",
    "public_key_ed25519":   "string — base64:ed25519-public-key"
  },

  "metadata": {
    "description": "string",
    "tags":        ["list of capability tags"],
    "registered_at_us": "integer"
  }
}
```

### 2.2 UID Convention

```
agt-{platform}-{role}-{index}

agt-wibo835-nav-001          Navigation agent, Wibo 835, instance 1
agt-wibo835-engine-001       Engine monitoring agent
agt-wibo835-power-001        Power management agent
agt-wibo835-comms-001        Communications agent
agt-wibo835-desktop-001      Desktop operator agent
agt-wibo835-sovereign-001    Sovereign orchestrator (highest tier)
```

### 2.3 AID Registration

On startup, every agent:

1. Generates or loads its Ed25519 keypair.
2. Constructs its AID including its public key.
3. Signs the AID with its private key.
4. Publishes an ANNOUNCE frame to `{platform}.meta.agent.{uid}`.
5. Begins publishing HEARTBEAT at `heartbeat_interval_s`.

