## 4. CM Message Types

All CM messages are ΣFrames. The `msg_type` field identifies the conversation act.

### 4.1 Lifecycle Messages

| Type | Sender | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `ANNOUNCE` | Agent | Publishes AID on startup or reconfiguration |
| `HEARTBEAT` | Agent | Liveness signal, includes current state and effective trust scores |
| `SHUTDOWN` | Agent | Graceful shutdown notification |

### 4.2 Negotiation Messages

| Type | Sender | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `PROPOSE` | Agent | Proposes an action or course change. Must include fallback. |
| `AGREE` | Agent | Accepts a PROPOSE from another agent |
| `REFUSE` | Agent | Rejects a PROPOSE, must include reason code |
| `RETRACT` | Agent | Withdraws a previous PROPOSE before TTL expiry |
| `COUNTER` | Agent | Counter-proposes alternative to a PROPOSE |

### 4.3 Control Messages

| Type | Sender | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `DELEGATE` | Sovereign/Operator | Transfers authority scope to another agent |
| `RESUME` | Any | Signals handback of previously delegated authority |
| `ALERT` | Any | Urgent broadcast, priority 1, bypasses normal queuing |

### 4.4 LLM Extension Messages

| Type | Sender | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `CONTEXT_SHARE` | Any | Shares compressed world model context with another agent |
| `UNCERTAINTY` | Agent | Declares reasoning uncertainty, requests escalation |
| `CRITIQUE` | Sovereign | Adversarial review of a PROPOSE before authorising actuation |
| `CONFIRM` | Any | Confirms successful execution of an action |
| `FAIL` | Any | Signals failed execution with reason |

### 4.5 PROPOSE Frame Structure

```json
{
  "msg_type": "PROPOSE",
  "sender":   "agt-wibo835-nav-001",
  "subject":  "wibo835.cmd.autopilot.heading",

  "payload": {
    "conversation_id":    "string (uuid-v4)",
    "proposed_action": {
      "path":    "wibo835.cmd.autopilot.heading",
      "value":   185.0,
      "unit":    "degrees_true",
      "duration_s": 300
    },
    "rationale": {
      "rule_applied":    "COLREG_RULE_16",
      "evidence_paths":  ["wibo835.nav.ais.target_987654321.cpa"],
      "evidence_values": {"cpa_nm": 0.28, "tcpa_min": 6.5}
    },
    "fallback": {
      "action":  "alter_course_starboard_20_deg",
      "trigger": "ttl_expiry",
      "autonomous": true
    },
    "ttl_us":              "integer — proposal expires at this time",
    "requires_agreement":  ["agt-wibo835-sovereign-001"],
    "step_confidence": {
      "internal_confidence_score": 0.96,
      "entropy_at_decision":       0.18
    }
  }
}
```

### 4.6 REFUSE Reason Codes

| Code | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `CONFIDENCE_BELOW_THRESHOLD` | Proposer's confidence < required minimum |
| `AUTHORITY_SCOPE_VIOLATION` | Proposed action outside proposer's authority |
| `HUMAN_OVERRIDE_ACTIVE` | Human override gate is active |
| `CONFLICTING_PROPOSAL` | A conflicting PROPOSE is already in negotiation |
| `INSUFFICIENT_EVIDENCE` | Evidence paths are stale or absent |
| `SAFETY_CONSTRAINT_VIOLATED` | Action would exceed physical limits (rudder, speed) |
| `TTL_EXPIRED` | PROPOSE TTL elapsed before agreement reached |

