## 7. Negotiation Protocol

### 7.1 Basic Proposal Flow

```
NavAgent                              SovereignAgent
    │                                      │
    │── PROPOSE ──────────────────────────►│
    │   conversation_id: uuid-1            │
    │   action: heading = 185°             │
    │   evidence: cpa=0.28nm, tcpa=6.5min  │
    │   fallback: alter +20° at ttl_expiry │
    │   ttl: now + 30s                     │
    │                                      │
    │                                ┌─────┴──────┐
    │                                │ CRITIQUE   │
    │                                │ evidence   │
    │                                │ confidence │
    │                                └─────┬──────┘
    │                                      │
    │◄─ AGREE ────────────────────────────│
    │   conversation_id: uuid-1            │
    │   authorised_action: heading = 185°  │
    │                                      │
    │── COMMAND ──────────────────────────►│ (cmd.autopilot.heading = 185)
    │                                      │
    │── CONFIRM ──────────────────────────►│
    │   conversation_id: uuid-1            │
    │   outcome: new_cpa = 0.85nm          │
```

### 7.2 CRITIQUE Check (before AGREE)

Before issuing AGREE, the receiving agent MUST perform:

```python
def critique_proposal(proposal: ProposeFrame) -> CritiqueResult:
    checks = [
        check_confidence(proposal.step_confidence.internal_confidence_score >= 0.80),
        check_evidence_trust(min(effective_trust(e) for e in proposal.evidence_paths) >= 0.60),
        check_authority(proposal.sender in allowed_proposers),
        check_scope(proposal.proposed_action.path in sender.authority_scope),
        check_physical_limits(proposal.proposed_action.value),
        check_human_override(),
    ]
    return CritiqueResult(all_passed=all(c.passed for c in checks), checks=checks)
```

### 7.3 Fallback Mandate

**Every PROPOSE must include a fallback.**

The fallback defines what happens if no agreement is reached before TTL expires.
It is never "do nothing" — that is a separate, explicit fallback value.

```json
"fallback": {
  "action":     "alter_course_starboard_20_deg | maintain_course | heave_to | anchor",
  "trigger":    "ttl_expiry | refuse_received | uncertainty_declared",
  "autonomous": true,
  "notify":     ["human_operator_vhf_ch16", "log_decision_journal"]
}
```

When a fallback executes, it is logged as a FAIL-SAFE event in the decision journal with
full provenance. It is not treated as a negotiation failure — it is normal protocol operation
in a time-critical environment.

### 7.4 Negotiation TTL

TTL (time-to-live) for a PROPOSE is mandatory. Recommended values:

| Scenario | TTL |
|---|---|
| Collision avoidance (CPA < 0.5nm, TCPA < 10min) | 10 – 30 s |
| Routine course change | 120 – 300 s |
| Engine parameter adjustment | 30 – 60 s |
| Anchoring / mooring | 300 – 600 s |

