## 8. Control Delegation — DELEGATE / RESUME

### 8.1 DELEGATE Frame

```json
{
  "msg_type": "DELEGATE",
  "sender":   "agt-wibo835-sovereign-001",

  "payload": {
    "conversation_id":  "uuid-v4",
    "assignee":         "agt-wibo835-nav-001",
    "authority_scope":  ["wibo835.cmd.autopilot.*"],
    "active_context_ref": "ctx-delta-1716123456",
    "valid_until_us":   "integer — hard expiry",
    "handback_triggers": [
      "uncertainty_declared",
      "human_override_active",
      "valid_until_us_reached",
      "cpa_below_0.3nm"
    ],
    "constraints": {
      "max_heading_change_deg": 40,
      "max_speed_change_kn":    2.0,
      "forbidden_paths":        []
    }
  }
}
```

### 8.2 RESUME Frame

```json
{
  "msg_type": "RESUME",
  "sender":   "agt-wibo835-nav-001",

  "payload": {
    "conversation_id": "uuid-of-original-delegate",
    "trigger":         "uncertainty_declared",
    "final_state": {
      "heading_set": 185.0,
      "cpa_at_handback_nm": 0.85
    }
  }
}
```

### 8.3 Delegation Rules

1. Only agents with `behavioral_trust ≥ 0.80` and `effective_trust ≥ 0.90` may receive DELEGATE.
2. Delegated authority is bounded by `constraints` — the delegate cannot exceed them.
3. DELEGATE has a hard `valid_until_us` expiry. After expiry, authority automatically reverts.
4. Any handback trigger fires RESUME automatically. The delegate does not decide when to hand back.
5. Delegation is never recursive — a delegate cannot re-delegate.

