## 9. LLM Integration Points

See `SIGMABUS-LLM-SPEC.md` for full specification. CM defines the message types;
the LLM spec defines the internal reasoning protocols.

### 9.1 UNCERTAINTY Message

Published by a Tier 1 agent when it detects its own reasoning is unreliable:

```json
{
  "msg_type": "UNCERTAINTY",
  "payload": {
    "conversation_id":   "uuid — the PROPOSE this uncertainty relates to",
    "context_reference": "ctx-delta-id — the context snapshot at failure point",
    "reason":            "entropy_threshold_exceeded | context_window_full | low_confidence",
    "entropy_at_trigger": 0.42,
    "handback_required":  true
  }
}
```

### 9.2 CONTEXT_SHARE Message

Used to pass compressed world model state from a higher-tier agent to a lower-tier agent:

```json
{
  "msg_type": "CONTEXT_SHARE",
  "payload": {
    "context_id":            "ctx-delta-1716123456",
    "target_scope":          "wibo835.nav.*",
    "compressed_state_delta": {
      "nav.position.gps_primary.lat":  51.9225,
      "nav.ais.target_987654321.cpa":  0.28,
      "agent.nav_agent.last_decision": "hold_course"
    },
    "token_count":    412,
    "compression":    "delta_from_last_known",
    "valid_until_us": 1716123486000000
  }
}
```

