## 11. Decision Journal

The decision journal is **load-bearing structure** — it is the mechanism by which every
autonomous action is traceable to its inputs. It is not a log file that can be deleted.

### 11.1 Journal Entry Schema

```json
{
  "journal_id":      "string (uuid-v4)",
  "conversation_id": "string — links to the PROPOSE/AGREE chain",
  "timestamp_us":    "integer",
  "event_type":      "PROPOSE | AGREE | REFUSE | DELEGATE | FALLBACK | CONFIRM | FAIL | OVERRIDE | CRITIQUE",

  "agent":           "string (agent UID)",
  "action_path":     "string (cmd.* path affected)",
  "action_value":    "any",

  "inputs": {
    "evidence_paths":  ["list of paths consulted"],
    "evidence_values": {"path": "value at decision time"},
    "evidence_trust":  {"path": "effective_trust at decision time"},
    "world_model_age_ms": "integer"
  },

  "reasoning": {
    "rule_applied":               "string or null",
    "internal_confidence_score":  "float",
    "entropy_at_decision":        "float",
    "alternatives_considered":    ["list of rejected alternatives"]
  },

  "outcome": {
    "result":         "SUCCESS | FAILURE | FALLBACK | OVERRIDE",
    "confirmed_at_us": "integer or null",
    "post_action_values": {"path": "value after action"}
  },

  "retention": "permanent"
}
```

### 11.2 Journal Persistence

- Stored in SQLite with `retention: permanent`.
- Never deleted automatically.
- Voyage-stamped for retrieval.
- Exported to human-readable markdown on voyage completion.

