## 13. Conformance

A CM implementation is conformant if it:

1. Implements all message types in §4 with correct fields.
2. Enforces the four-dimension trust model (§6) without collapsing dimensions.
3. Requires a fallback in every PROPOSE (§7.3).
4. Enforces CRITIQUE checks before issuing AGREE (§7.2).
5. Implements the human override gate as a structural enforcement layer, not agent logic (§10).
6. Persists behavioral trust across sessions (§6.4).
7. Writes every decision to the decision journal with full provenance (§11).
8. Enforces delegation rules (§8.3) including the no-recursive-delegation rule.
